# Neural Inverse Firmware — Production Gap Analysis vs Embedder

## The Problem

Embedder's UVP (from their own words):

> **"Pre-configured AI agent that can read your MCU's datasheet, write firmware, flash it, and verify it works on real hardware — out of the box."**

The closed loop is: **Write code → Flash it → Read serial output → Debug it → Fix it** — all without leaving the conversation.

We have services and types, but **none of them actually execute**. Our implementation is interface-rich but execution-poor.

---

## Gap Analysis: Embedder vs Us (Honest Assessment)

| Capability | Embedder | Neural Inverse | Gap |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Hardware-aware context** | ✅ Knows MCU, has TRM loaded | ⚠️ Context provider exists but no firmware system prompt in Power Mode agent | **Agent doesn't know it's a firmware agent** |
| **Register-level intelligence** | ✅ SVD lookup, bit fields, access types | ✅ SVD parser + register tools work | Close to parity |
| **Serial monitor** | ✅ Reads/writes serial in real-time, inline in chat | ⚠️ Web Serial API foundation but no Power Mode integration | **Serial data doesn't reach the agent** |
| **Build & Flash** | ✅ Runs builds, parses errors, flashes | ⚠️ Build commands are emitted but never executed | **No actual execution** |
| **Datasheet/TRM search** | ✅ Semantic search across loaded docs | ⚠️ Extraction pipeline exists, no semantic search | **No query engine** |
| **GDB debugging** | ✅ Drives GDB, reads device state, step-through | ❌ Zero debug support | **Missing entirely** |
| **Domain-tuned reasoning** | ✅ Firmware-specific system prompt | ❌ Generic agent prompt, firmware context is side-band | **Agent needs firmware identity** |
| **Platform skills** | ✅ Pre-built workflows for STM32, nRF, AURIX, ESP32 | ❌ No platform-specific knowledge packs | **Missing entirely** |
| **Session persistence** | ✅ Remembers MCU, project, port across restarts | ⚠️ Basic storage but doesn't restore SVD/datasheets | **Partial — no reload** |
| **Project auto-setup** | ✅ Auto-detects everything, zero config | ⚠️ Project detector exists, doesn't trigger SVD loading | **Doesn't complete the loop** |
| **Integrated context** | ✅ MCU + serial + docs + project as unified picture | ⚠️ Each service is isolated silo | **No cross-service orchestration** |
| **Hardware-in-the-loop** | ✅ Write→build→flash→serial→debug in one session | ❌ No workflow orchestration | **Missing entirely** |

