## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **GDB integration strategy**: Should we drive GDB through the integrated terminal (like Embedder) or create a dedicated DAP (Debug Adapter Protocol) integration? DAP is more VS Code-native but requires more infrastructure. Terminal-based GDB is faster to ship and matches what Embedder does.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Electron IPC for serial ports**: The Web Serial API works in Chromium but has permission limitations. For production, we may need an Electron main process bridge using the `serialport` npm package for reliable port enumeration and access. Should this be Phase A or deferred?

> [!WARNING]
> **Firmware system prompt activation**: When a firmware session is active, should Power Mode ALWAYS use the firmware prompt (replacing the generic one), or should we add a firmware-specific agent mode that users explicitly switch to (like Plan Mode vs Build Mode)?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Platform skills scope**: How many platforms should we ship in v1? Embedder supports STM32, nRF/Zephyr, AURIX, ESP32, C2000, NXP, Renesas, Microchip. We have MCU database entries for many but zero platform skill content. Recommend: STM32 + ESP32 + nRF + RP2040 for v1.

